OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA bright start in the east, but
OL,6,Frather cloudy with showery outbreaks
OL,7,Fof rain further west. The showers
OL,8,Fbecoming more widespread into the
OL,9,Fafternoon and turning persistent
OL,10,Flater. Still rather warm and humid.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FRain will become persistent
OL,13,Fovernight with some heavier bursts
OL,14,Flikely across eastern counties. The
OL,15,Frain should clear southern areas for a
OL,16,Ftime towards dawn.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
